Add Images and Files to Email Messages in the Salesforce Classic Case Feed

Give customers comprehensive information to help resolve their issues more quickly by attaching files to email messages, and add inline images to include pictures that enhance your text.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
User permissions needed: Send Email

To send emails with attachments or inline images:

* Click  in the toolbar of the Case Feed email publisher and upload or link to the image you want. Each image must be no larger than 1 MB.
* To attach files, click Upload files to choose a file from your computer or Salesforce, or drag files to the attachments area at the bottom of the email publisher. You can attach up to 10 MB to each email message.

When the recipient views the message, any images you've embedded appear in the body of the email.. If the total size of everything is greater than 3 MB, all attachments appear as links, which the recipient can use to download the files.

Example: Attach a how-to video or document with multiple sets of detailed troubleshooting steps. Use inline images after each step in the body of a message.

See also:

* Send and Reply to Email in the Salesforce Classic Case Feed
* Find, Attach, and Email Articles with the Case Feed Articles Tool
* Customize Emails with the Rich Text Editor in the Salesforce Classic Case Feed
title: Adding Images and Files to Email Messages
